---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Nav } from "@/components/landing/Nav";
import { Footer } from "@/components/landing/Footer";

const LAST_UPDATED = "July 4, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service - Loopress WordPress Developer Tools"
  description="The terms governing use of the Loopress CLI, WordPress plugin, and console, currently in alpha."
  canonical="https://loopress.dev/terms"
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background text-foreground">
    <Nav client:load />
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-24">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
        Loopress is currently in alpha. These terms cover the CLI, the WordPress plugin,
        and the Loopress console. By using any of them, you agree to what's below. Questions?
        <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground">Contact us</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">The service</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The Loopress CLI and WordPress plugin are open source, licensed under the
            <a href="https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/MPL/2.0/" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground">Mozilla Public License 2.0</a>.
            You can inspect, self-host, and modify them under that license. The Loopress console
            (<a href="https://console.loopress.dev" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground">console.loopress.dev</a>)
            is a hosted service, currently free during the alpha.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Alpha status</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The console is in active development. Features, limits, and pricing described on this
            site may change without notice. We don't guarantee uptime or data durability during
            the alpha, and recommend keeping your own backups of anything Loopress manages on your
            WordPress sites.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Your account</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            You're responsible for the WordPress application passwords and Loopress account
            credentials you use with the service, and for any activity performed with your
            projects. Application passwords are scoped by WordPress itself; revoke one at any
            time from your site's admin if you suspect it's compromised.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Acceptable use</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Use Loopress to manage WordPress sites you're authorized to administer. Don't use it
            to attack, scan, or gain unauthorized access to sites you don't control, and don't
            abuse the console's infrastructure (excessive automated load, credential stuffing,
            and similar).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Fees</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The CLI and plugin are free and open source. The console is free during the alpha.
            Paid tiers (Pro, Agency) are planned; if you're on one when it launches, separate
            billing terms will apply and you'll be asked to accept them before being charged.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Loopress is provided "as is," without warranties of any kind, express or implied,
            including fitness for a particular purpose. You're responsible for testing changes
            (snippets, plugins, dependencies) before applying them to a production site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Limitation of liability</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To the extent permitted by law, Loopress is not liable for indirect, incidental, or
            consequential damages arising from use of the CLI, plugin, or console, including data
            loss on a WordPress site you manage with them.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Termination</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            You can stop using Loopress and delete your account at any time via the
            <a href="/contact" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-foreground">contact page</a>.
            We may suspend console access for accounts that violate the acceptable use terms above.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-foreground">Changes to these terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We'll update this page as the product moves out of alpha and paid plans launch, and
            update the date at the top when we do.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
